  "title": "Apple Q3 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-10-30T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q3",
  "location": "Cupertino, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.apple.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "tim-cook",
      "speaker_name": "Tim Cook",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "We had an exceptional Q3. Services reached $29.1 billion, up 15%, with Apple TV+, Apple Arcade, and iCloud all achieving records. India manufacturing now accounts for over 20% of all iPhone units sold globally, up from 14% a year ago. iPhone 17 will begin shipping September 19th — I've never been more excited about a product launch. Apple Intelligence features in iPhone 17 include real-time translation, personalized Siri actions, and on-device image generation."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "kevan-parekh",
      "speaker_name": "Kevan Parekh",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Q3 revenue was $93.7 billion, up 6% year-over-year. Gross margin was 48.1%, the highest in over five years. We returned $29.5 billion to shareholders. For Q4 2025, we expect revenue of $91–94 billion and gross margin of 47.5–48.5%. We are tracking toward full-year Services revenue above $110 billion."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Ben Reitzes at Melius Research."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-ben-reitzes",
      "speaker_name": "Ben Reitzes",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Tim, gross margin at 48.1% is remarkable. How much of that is India manufacturing cost savings versus Services mix shift, and is this the new floor for margins?"
    }
  ],
